# A.I.N.D.Y. Apps Monolith — Environment Variable Reference
#
# This repo is a plugin layer on top of aindy-runtime. The runtime reads its
# env from AINDY/.env inside the installed package (or from the path set by
# AINDY_ENV_FILE). For local dev against a sibling checkout, the simplest
# approach is to set AINDY_ENV_FILE to point at a .env in this repo root:
#
#   export AINDY_ENV_FILE=$(pwd)/.env
#   aindy-runtime-api     # reads .env from this directory
#
# For the full env var reference (Redis, event bus, quotas, etc.) see:
#   ../aindy-runtime/AINDY/.env.example
#
# This file documents only the vars you must set for the monolith to boot.
# DO NOT commit .env to version control.


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Group 1 — Required for any boot
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

DATABASE_URL=
# Required. PostgreSQL connection URI.
#   postgresql://aindy:aindy@localhost:5432/aindy   (local dev)
#   postgresql://aindy:aindy@postgres:5432/aindy    (Docker Compose)
# SQLite (sqlite://) is accepted only for unit tests — set AINDY_ALLOW_SQLITE=1.

SECRET_KEY=REPLACE_THIS_with_a_32_char_hex_string
# Required. JWT signing key — minimum 32 characters outside test/dev.
# Generate: python3 -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"

OPENAI_API_KEY=
# Required for memory embeddings and LLM calls.
# Development: empty logs a warning but the server still boots.
# Production: runtime refuses to boot if unset or a known placeholder.

PERMISSION_SECRET=REPLACE_THIS_with_a_32_char_hex_string
# Required. App-layer permission signing key — keep separate from SECRET_KEY.
# Generate: python3 -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Group 2 — Plugin manifest
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# AINDY_APP_PLUGIN_MANIFEST=./aindy_plugins.json
# Path to the app plugin manifest. Defaults to ./aindy_plugins.json relative
# to the working directory. Only set this if running aindy-runtime-api from
# a directory other than this repo root.


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Group 3 — Optional / commonly overridden
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:5173
# Comma-separated CORS origins. Add your frontend dev server origin here.
# Production: replace with your actual deployment origin(s).

DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
# Optional. Only needed if workflows route LLM calls to DeepSeek.

AINDY_API_KEY=
# Optional. Bearer token for machine-to-machine calls to this runtime's API.

# MONGO_URL=mongodb://localhost:27017
# Required only if social layer or memory backends use Mongo.
# Leave unset to run without Mongo (MONGO_REQUIRED defaults to false).

# MONGO_DB_NAME=aindy_social_layer
# Mongo database name used by the social layer (posts, profiles, comments,
# metrics history) and Mongo-backed services. Defaults to "aindy_default" if
# unset. ALL social-layer code resolves the database from this single var, so
# the value only has to be consistent — but set it explicitly to match your
# deployment (production uses "aindy_social_layer").

# SOCIAL_FEED_BRIDGE_ORIGINS=system
# Comma-separated allowlist of bridge-event `origin` values surfaced in the
# social feed's `events` channel. Defaults to "system". Blank/unset-to-blank
# surfaces nothing (safe default). Widen once you know which origins are
# system/public (e.g. "system,scheduler").

# REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0
# Required for distributed execution mode, event bus, and cache.
# Thread mode (the default) runs without Redis.


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Group 4 — Local dev overrides
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ENV=development
# AINDY_ALLOW_SQLITE=
# AINDY_SKIP_MONGO_PING=
# SKIP_MONGO_PING=
# LOG_LEVEL=INFO
